The probability of treatment failure was estimated for given: hair concentration level (X1), self-reported adherence measured by visual analogue scale (VAS) (X2), BMI-for-age (X3) categorised in three groups as underweight (<5th percentile), normal (5th to <95th percentile) and underweight (≥ 95th percentile), follow-up event (X4), and participant caregiver status (X5) using the “predict” function in R-statistical package which apply eq. 2, where β0 is the estimated regression constant, β1, β2, β3, β4 and β5 are the estimated regression coefficients for X1, X2, X3,X4 and X5 variables, respectively:
